text: The Modernize and Innovate the Delivery of Agricultural Systems (MIDAS) program will
label: BODY

text: transform Farm Service Agency's (FSA) delivery of Farm Program benefits, on behalf of the
label: BODY

text: Commodity Credit Corporation (CCC), into a 21st century business model. This project will
label: BODY

text: provide capability to meet the increasing demand for customer self-service and eliminate
label: BODY

text: FSA's reliance on aging technology. This project will reduce the risk of hardware failure by
label: BODY

text: replacing the farm program applications residing on the outdated AS400/S36 computing
label: BODY

text: platform with an integrated COTS solution, SAP. This project will reengineer business
label: BODY

text: processes to be common and centralize data assets to support farm programs, eliminate
label: BODY

text: program specific duplication of functionality and non-integrated, distributed data that exists
label: BODY

text: between farm program software applications. It will accomplish increased compliance with
label: BODY

text: modern internal control structures and effectively implement improved IT security. MIDAS will
label: BODY

text: install commitment-based accounting practices (e.g., obligations, commitments, outlays,
label: BODY

text: funds control) to upgrade both the program and financial management business practices of
label: BODY

text: the CCC. The project is intended to align with Office of the Chief Financial Officer's (OCFO)
label: BODY

label: BODY
